priorities.title: Verify Document Matches
priorities.description: All 2,374 document-to-person matches are unverified. Review and confirm these connections.

priorities.title: Match Unlinked Documents
priorities.description: 790 documents with readable text aren't connected to anyone. These may contain names, dates, or places for existing or new people.

priorities.title: Resolve Potential Duplicates
priorities.description: 35 pairs of people have similar names and dates — they may be the same person entered twice.

priorities.title: Find Census Records
priorities.description: 1,105 people have dates and places but no census record. US Census records (1790-1950) could fill major gaps.

priorities.title: Find Missing Parents
priorities.description: 589 people (47%) have no parents linked. Extending these lines backward is the core of genealogy.

priorities.title: Find Obituaries
priorities.description: 849 people with death dates have no obituary. Obituaries often name parents, children, and siblings.

priorities.title: Fix Data Anomalies
priorities.description: 37 records have suspicious dates — impossible parent ages, deaths before births, or people living 120+ years.

priorities.title: Consolidate Surname Spellings
priorities.description: 75 surname groups have multiple spellings (Fry/Frye, Dunkleberger/Dunkelberger, etc.). Standardizing improves search.

priorities.title: Add Missing Documents
priorities.description: 620 people (49%) have no documents at all. Photos, certificates, or records would strengthen their profiles.
